remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` represents a four-byte OpenType/TrueType tag packed into a 32-bit
unsigned integer, with the first character in the high byte and the fourth in the
low byte. Tags identify font tables (e.g., `name`, `cmap`), variation axes
(e.g., `wght`, `wdth`), and other OpenType features.

The string form of a tag is exactly four ASCII characters. When parsing shorter
strings with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag.Parse(System.String)>, the value is
padded with spaces.

`SKFourByteTag` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Parse a tag from a string
var wght = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");

// Construct from individual characters
var wdth = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'd', 't', 'h');

// Convert back to string
Console.WriteLine(wght.ToString()); // "wght"

// Use as uint
uint raw = wght;
```
